1.  Check the README file is still relevant

Please do the following, or run release_amarok:

2.  Checkout a fresh copy of amarok, its docs and po; cd into the root
3.  Update APP_VERSION in amarok/src/amarok.h
4.  Update the version in amarok/amarok.lsm
5.  find -name CVS -o -name .cvsignore -exec rm {} \;
6.  export WANT_AUTOMAKE=1.6
7.  make -f Makefile.cvs
8.  rm -rf autom4te.cache config.h config.log
9.  pushd amarok; mv README TODO INSTALL ChangeLog AUTHORS ..; popd
10. mv ../kdeextragear-1 ../amarok-VERSION
11. tar cjf ../amarok-VERSION.tar.bz2 ../amarok-VERSION
12. Test for default configure, --enable-final, separate build directory
13. Get some other people to test

Once HAPPY with the tarball:

13. Upload to ftp://upload.sf.net/incoming
14. Release via sourceforge
15. Update kde-apps.org, freshmeat, amarok.kde.org
16. Send a release email to kde-announce, libvisual-devel, kde-multimedia, etc.
17. Drink a few pints, have some fun on #amarok

If you must change anything about the tarball you need to email
binner@kde.org in case the md5sum changing would break Konstruct.

